ROLE: RE-REVIEW of a fix for a FINAL REVIEW BLOCK on browserplex bead browserplex-2mv (P0, electron
session type). Round-1 final review: agy PASS, Opus PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUPS, Codex **BLOCK**.

PHASE: review (re-review of the changed part)
DECISION STANDARD: BLOCK | PASS | PASS_WITH_FOLLOWUPS.

THE BLOCK (Codex, verified CORRECT against Playwright source electron.js:142-175): without
`executablePath`, Playwright resolves Electron via `require("electron/index.js")` from ITS OWN
install (browserplex's node_modules), NOT from `cwd` — `cwd` is only the spawn working dir. So the
plan's premise "drives the target app's electron via cwd, no runtime dep" was false; and since
`electron` is a devDependency, a production `npm i browserplex` would have no electron at all.

THE FIX (diff below):
1. Added `executablePath` to ElectronLaunchOptions, actions.sessionCreate, and the session_create
   MCP schema — this selects WHICH electron binary launches (point at the app's
   node_modules/.bin/electron). `cwd` re-documented as spawn working dir only.
2. README corrected: explicit note that browserplex ships electron only as a DEV dependency and users
   must set `executablePath` to their app's electron; the example now sets executablePath.
3. New test `honors an explicit executablePath` launches via `executablePath = require('electron')`,
   proving the param is plumbed to _electron.launch (answers Codex's "fixture masks it").
4. (Already folded, also an Opus follow-up) the post-launch path is wrapped in try/catch calling
   `app.close()` if firstWindow()/context() throws — no orphaned Electron on partial launch.

RE-VERIFICATION: build clean; electron tests 2/2 (default path + explicit executablePath); full
suite 70/70.

JUDGE ONLY THE FIX: Does adding executablePath correctly address the binary-resolution gap? Is the
documentation now accurate (executablePath selects the binary; cwd is working dir; electron is
dev-only)? Does the executablePath test meaningfully prove the plumbing? Is the try/catch leak guard
correct? Any new regression?

